.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2023" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a basic shell implementation by Brandon Montezuma and Manning Stinson

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fICOMMAND [ARGUMENTS]\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsimple_shell\fR is a lightweight and interactive shell designed for basic command-line operations.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h, --help
Display help message and exit.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR ls
List files and directories in the current directory.

.TP
.BR cd \fIDIRECTORY\fR
Change the current working directory to \fIDIRECTORY\fR.

.TP
.BR cp \fIFILE SOURCE DESTINATION\fR
Copy \fIFILE\fR from \fISOURCE\fR to \fIDESTINATION\fR.

.TP
.BR mv \fIFILE SOURCE DESTINATION\fR
Move \fIFILE\fR from \fISOURCE\fR to \fIDESTINATION\fR.

.TP
.BR rm \fIFILE\fR
Remove (\fIDELETE\fR) \fIFILE\fR.

.TP
.BR echo \fIARGUMENTS\fR
Print \fIARGUMENTS\fR to the standard output.

.TP
.BR string \fISTRING1 STRING2\fR
Concatenate \fISTRING1\fR and \fISTRING2\fR.

.TP
.BR history
Display command history.

.TP
.BR help
Display help information.

.TP
.BR exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.BR alias \fIALIAS_NAME COMMAND\fR
Create an alias for \fICOMMAND\fR with the name \fIALIAS_NAME\fR.

.SH USAGE
To use \fBsimple_shell\fR, simply run the executable with the desired command.

.P
For example:
.B simple_shell ls -l

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B simple_shell ls -l
List the contents of the current directory in long format.

.TP
.B simple_shell alias ll ls -l
Create an alias \fBll\fR for \fBls -l\fR.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.B simple_shell
exits with the exit status of the executed command or 0 if no command is provided.

.SH AUTHORS
This shell was developed by Brandon Montezuma and Manning Stinson.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash (1),
.BR sh (1),
.BR dash (1).

.SH BUGS
Report any bugs to your.email@example.com.

